The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 Birla Sun Life Insurance has unveiled Life Companion Plan. The plan will offer market-linked returns with an equity component of 25 per cent in the investment fund and will give 5 per cent of the maturity benefits as loyalty additions. The minimum and maximum entry age is 30 days and 65 years, respectively. For the money-back option, one can choose policy terms of 16, 20 and 24 years with money-back intervals of four years, while for endowment, it is 15, 20, 25 and 30 years.

 PruICICI has launched PruICICI Infrastructure Fund, which will invest in stocks of infrastructure companies. The minimum application amount in the fund is Rs 5000. For investments below Rs 5 crore, the fund will charge an entry load of 2.25 per cent and an exit load of 1 per cent if redeemed within six months. The new fund offer will remain open till August 10.

 HDFC Mutual Fund has launched HDFC Multiple Yield Fund. The fund will invest around 85 per cent of the corpus in fixed income instruments and the remaining in equity stocks. For investment less than or equal to Rs 2 crore, there is an exit load of 1 per cent, if the units are redeemed within 15 months. The new fund offer is open till August 1.




